<br>
CHA will effect mezes so always CHA buff yourself.   As another enchanter mentioned, keep int and cha fairly balanced -- myself I&quot;m at 255 cha, and 251 int.  <br>
<br>
AoE mez - I have it up outdoors sometimes, never indoors.  Most dungeons in game I tend to mez myself.   THere appears to be many tactics though so it's all a matter of getting a handle on things.  I can mez trains of up to 12 to 15 frogs in Sebilis with dazzle and chain AE stunning.  The agro comment on ae stunning was interesting, but I feel it's negligable...root is far worse imho.  AE stuns have always bought me the time I needed, even in the revamped CT...agro is insane in there anyway so I have agro spells up and mem blurr, and I pray regularly hehe jk.   <br>
<br>
Another issue is maxing all your spell skills out so you can channel through being attacked.  If you have even one of your spell skills at a weak level I've found it effects you greatly.  Mez is conjuration based so check that skill out specifically.  I find that well over 70 percent of the time I can channel through agro.<br>
<br>
The mem blurr technique is very very good, but if you have an MT that knows what they are doing it's not mana efficient.   I personally go with agro spells over mem blurr series.  I love the new agro spells -- saved my arse many a time.<br>
<br>
In the end there are lots of ways to play an enchanter, and some really good advice on this board.  Another issue that you are running in to is the fact that 90 percent of healers don't know how to heal enchanters.  Especially in your low 40's I would say that goes way up.  It's only been since I was above level 55 that I was able to find clerics who knew how to time heals on a chanter, so just as you are getting your cc timing down at your level, your clerics are getting their healing timing down at this level too.<br>
<br>
Certainly sounds like you are off to a good start -- 2 resists in 7 is a bit high imho, so I would check your cha...higher cha may make it 1 resist in 7 which can make a huge difference -- even though it seems like a small  number.  I believe the actual figure is 5 percent fewer resists per 50 cha.  It's a small number, and results in 1 or 2 fewer resists in 10 mobs, but it's easy to get higher cha, and worth it imho.<br>
<br>
Have fun =)<br>
<br>
